         <Properties>
            <Property Name="AutoExpandLevels">
               <Summary>his property is used if you want the topmost nodes in the tree automatically expanded.</Summary>
               <Desc>The default value is -1 and it means that no nodes are expanded. Another value will expands all nodes with Level less than or to AutoExpandLevels when they are first created.
                  <P>Note</P>
                  <P>When you set AutoExpandLevels property all existing nodes in the tree will expand or collapse depending on the value and their level.</P>
               </Desc>
            </Property>
            <Property Name="BoldHandle">
               <Summary>The BoldHandle property indicates which handle the control should follow. </Summary>
               <Desc>Since TBoldCustomTreeView starts with a single element as the root for a tree it will follow the Value property of the handle. Note that for a TBoldListHandle this means the current element in the list. </Desc>
            </Property>
            <Property Name="BoldProperties">
               <Summary>This property has a number of sub-properties that control the Bold-aware aspects of the control. </Summary>
               <Desc> </Desc>
            </Property>
            <Property Name="CurrentElement">
               <Summary></Summary>
               <Desc></Desc>
            </Property>
            <Property Name="CurrentFollower">
               <Summary></Summary>
               <Desc></Desc>
            </Property>
            <Property Name="MaxLevels">
               <Summary>his property controls how deep you can drill down in a branch. </Summary>
               <Desc>The default value is -1 and it doesn't imply any constraints. Another value will prevent nodes on MaxLevel from expanding.
                  <P>Note</P>
                  <P>When you the set MaxLevels property existing nodes will be deleted if they have a Level higher than MaxLevel.</P>
               </Desc>
            </Property>
